WEBVTT

00:00.735 --> 00:06.438
Distinguished guests,
my fellow americans,

00:06.440 --> 00:08.741
It is a great honor
and privilege

00:08.743 --> 00:11.110
For me to be here
with you today.

00:11.112 --> 00:13.579
Today we remember
and say goodbye

00:13.581 --> 00:17.649
To a man who
loved his country, madly.

00:17.651 --> 00:20.152
A man who worked to better
his country, profoundly...

00:20.154 --> 00:23.288
[ cellphone ringing ]

00:26.459 --> 00:29.094
Cyrus:
<i>You've reached cyrus beene.</i>
<i>Please leave a message.</i>

00:29.096 --> 00:34.199
Woman:
A 62-year-old male with multiple
penetrating wounds to the chest.

00:34.201 --> 00:36.568
Poorly responsive
and hypotensive

00:36.570 --> 00:39.238
With a b.P. Of 60/30
and dropping fast.

00:39.240 --> 00:40.639
I'm telling you
something's up.

00:40.641 --> 00:42.174
Why isn't the president
there yet?

00:42.176 --> 00:44.643
And I'm telling you
to stay calm. He'll be here.

00:44.645 --> 00:47.679
[ beep ]

00:47.681 --> 00:50.082
Fitz: A soldier on
the battle lines of immigration,

00:50.084 --> 00:55.087
Rob worked tirelessly
to mend a broken system.

00:55.089 --> 00:56.488
Cy?

00:58.124 --> 01:00.726
You okay?

01:00.728 --> 01:02.061
There's a thing, sir.
There's a thing --

01:02.063 --> 01:04.163
A thing
I need to tell you.

01:04.165 --> 01:08.333
Mr. President.
We have a situation.

01:19.512 --> 01:21.447
[ gasps ]

01:21.449 --> 01:24.483
Man: I've got governor ashland
going towards the east gate.

01:24.485 --> 01:26.452
Senator marquez, secure!
Go! Go! Go!

01:26.454 --> 01:28.187
[ indistinct shouting ]

01:28.189 --> 01:31.490
[ siren wails ]

01:31.492 --> 01:33.525
Ashland, clear.
Marquez, clear.

01:33.527 --> 01:35.627
Evac's at 75% percent,
sir.

01:35.629 --> 01:37.729
It's a miracle we caught this
in time. Isn't it, cyrus?

01:37.731 --> 01:39.565
Tanner:
<i>Vice president sally langston</i>
<i>was in attendance,</i>

01:39.567 --> 01:41.600
<i>As well as the republican</i>
<i>vice presidential nominee,</i>

01:41.602 --> 01:43.669
<i>California governor</i>
<i>andrew nichols.</i>

01:43.671 --> 01:45.804
<i>The president, thankfully,</i>
<i>had not yet arrived</i>

01:45.806 --> 01:48.140
<i>When authorities began</i>
<i>the evacuation.</i>

01:48.142 --> 01:50.642
You're absolutely sure
there's a bomb in that building?
Yes, sir.

01:50.644 --> 01:52.778
Absolutely sure?
100% percent, sir.

01:52.780 --> 01:55.647
We're gonna look like
a bunch of --

01:55.649 --> 01:57.449
[ screaming ]

02:08.461 --> 02:10.362
Man: We've got governor nichols.
Where's the v.P.?
Where's sally?

02:10.364 --> 02:12.131
We do not have eyes
on the v.P., sir.

02:12.133 --> 02:14.633
Shut down air traffic.
Woman: Yes, sir.

02:14.635 --> 02:16.568
I want a sweep of the
capitol, pentagon, every
major tourist site.

02:16.570 --> 02:18.237
On it, sir.
Eyes on the v.P.! Eyes on!

02:18.239 --> 02:20.706
We have her on the move.

02:20.708 --> 02:22.674
Once sec!
Approaching motorcade!
We have to move, sir!

02:22.676 --> 02:25.544
Not yet!
Leo!
I have orders!

02:25.546 --> 02:27.679
One second!

02:27.681 --> 02:30.516
Just --
I need one sec! Hey!

02:30.518 --> 02:32.684
This is it, sally.

02:32.686 --> 02:35.220
This is your pearl harbor,
your 9/11, your act of god.

02:35.222 --> 02:37.389
This is your time.
[ police radio chatter ]

02:37.391 --> 02:39.691
[ indistinct shouting ]

02:39.693 --> 02:42.227
Agent. Hold the car.
Man: Yes, ma'am.

02:42.229 --> 02:45.631
Wait, wait, wait.
Wait, wait.

02:47.901 --> 02:51.637
Be jesus. You go in there,
and you be jesus!

02:53.873 --> 02:55.574
Man:
Still no indication

02:55.576 --> 02:59.244
Woman: Could be domestic.
We're looking into fringe
religious groups --

02:59.246 --> 03:00.946
Mr. President, we need to get
you into the briefing room.

03:00.948 --> 03:03.315
Not until we get answers.
There'll be time
for that later.

03:03.317 --> 03:06.351
Right now,
we need to get you out there.
Excuse me.

03:06.353 --> 03:08.854
[ indistinct conversations ]

03:10.523 --> 03:12.524
Olivia, you have blood
on your shirt.

03:12.526 --> 03:13.692
Why do you
have blood on your shirt?

03:13.694 --> 03:16.628
My father was stabbed.
Maya? Is rowan --

03:16.630 --> 03:18.764
He's in the hospital.
I don't know how he is.

03:18.766 --> 03:21.600
All I know is that right now,
you need to be

03:21.602 --> 03:23.769
In front of a camera
addressing the nation, now.

03:23.771 --> 03:27.506
Because the next few hours
are crucial to your re-election.

03:27.508 --> 03:29.308
Leo: Well, the secret service
tried to drag her out of here,

03:29.310 --> 03:32.377
I mean, you know she volunteered
for the red cross after college?

03:32.379 --> 03:36.815
Madame vice president,
can you tell us h-how --

03:36.817 --> 03:38.383
Not now. There's too much work
to be done here.

03:38.385 --> 03:41.787
Can you help me apply
some pressure?
Of course.

03:41.789 --> 03:42.955
[ camera shutter clicking ]

03:42.957 --> 03:45.490
No cameras, please.

03:45.492 --> 03:47.693
No, no, no, no, no. Keep --
keep rolling. It's okay.

03:47.695 --> 03:50.462
For history.

03:50.464 --> 03:52.598
Although we're clearly just
beginning our investigation,

03:52.600 --> 03:55.300
I want to assure
the american people

03:55.302 --> 03:58.470
Whoever was responsible
for this attack

03:58.472 --> 04:00.839
Will be brought to justice.

04:00.841 --> 04:03.709
The United States
will not tolerate

04:03.711 --> 04:05.911
Nor will its citizens
be intimidated...

04:05.913 --> 04:08.680
I'm looking at a split screen,
tracey!

04:08.682 --> 04:10.282
Why the hell am I looking
at a split screen?!

04:10.284 --> 04:11.283
The election
has nothing to do with it.

04:11.285 --> 04:14.386
You don't put the president
of the United States

04:14.388 --> 04:15.721
On a split screen.
B.N.C.

04:15.723 --> 04:19.024
Jim, the country wants to hear
from their president.

04:19.026 --> 04:21.793
You're a news organization.
Act like it.

04:21.795 --> 04:25.797
Some talking head
on a Sunday-morning news show!

04:25.799 --> 04:29.301
Oh, we've got a full screen!
That did not just happen!

04:29.303 --> 04:31.837
Annie! Annie, you dropped
the president?! Annie?! Annie?!
Another one.

04:31.839 --> 04:34.439
Tracey, full screen
on the veep? Really?
Another one down.

04:34.441 --> 04:37.576
I will spend the rest of my life
making sure you pay for this.

04:37.578 --> 04:39.344
Jim. You can do this.
Show your integrity.

04:39.346 --> 04:42.814
Be a leader. Give the president
the respect he deserves.

04:42.816 --> 04:45.984
Don't apologize.
Just don't do it.

04:45.986 --> 04:47.653
Don't you dare!

04:47.655 --> 04:51.590
Jim. I mean it.
Don't you d--

04:52.692 --> 04:53.925
[ sighs ]

04:58.031 --> 04:59.931
Sally: Just as saint francis
built his church --

04:59.933 --> 05:02.801
Brick by brick
and stone by stone --

05:02.803 --> 05:04.936
The brave americans
who suffered here today

05:04.938 --> 05:06.772
Will have to rebuild
their lives.

05:06.774 --> 05:08.740
But they will not do it alone.

05:08.742 --> 05:11.410
Every american will be
with them.

05:11.412 --> 05:14.579
<i>I</i> will be with them.

05:14.581 --> 05:17.883
And make no mistake -- we will
not turn the other cheek.

05:17.885 --> 05:19.418
We will find out
whoever did this,

05:19.420 --> 05:21.887
And we will be just,
and we will be swift,

05:21.889 --> 05:23.455
And we will be ruthless.

05:23.457 --> 05:26.625
Now let us pray.

05:32.332 --> 05:34.833
You see it?

05:34.835 --> 05:36.935
I saw it.

05:39.439 --> 05:42.074
You know I never give up.

05:42.076 --> 05:46.378
Yeah, I -- I know.
[ sighs ]

05:46.380 --> 05:51.016
We're gonna lose the election
on Tuesday.

05:51.018 --> 05:53.352
Let's be honest.

05:53.354 --> 05:55.454
We lost the election today.

06:00.694 --> 06:05.864
That was before
sally's canonization.
[ chuckles ]

06:05.866 --> 06:07.666
What about the bombers?
What about them?

06:07.668 --> 06:10.135
We March them
in front of some cameras.

06:10.137 --> 06:11.703
It won't make a difference.
It's too late.

06:11.705 --> 06:14.139
What if we hit the road?
Florida, ohio, pennsylvania.

06:14.141 --> 06:15.941
It won't be enough.
I'll give some big speeches.

06:15.943 --> 06:18.009
We'll steal back
the headlines.
Olivia: I'm sorry.

06:18.011 --> 06:21.680
I know how much
this meant to you.

06:26.018 --> 06:27.919
I'm gonna lose?

06:30.990 --> 06:34.159
Mellie:
I want a refund.

06:34.161 --> 06:35.494
I want our money back.

06:35.496 --> 06:37.462
Whatever your fee is,

06:37.464 --> 06:40.665
Whatever ridiculous amount
of money we have wasted on you.
Fitz: Mellie...

06:40.667 --> 06:42.134
Why did we hire her?!

06:42.136 --> 06:44.102
'cause I thought
we hired her to win.

06:48.908 --> 06:51.510
[ monitor beeping ]

06:58.751 --> 07:00.352
Hmm.

07:00.354 --> 07:03.088
The doctors
said you're a miracle.

07:03.090 --> 07:06.925
Said the knife came
this close to your heart.

07:06.927 --> 07:09.428
I'm alive,
and that's what matters.

07:13.132 --> 07:16.568
I'm glad you're okay.

07:19.539 --> 07:21.940
What's wrong?

07:24.444 --> 07:27.446
Nothing.

07:27.448 --> 07:30.215
I was...
Worried about you.

07:30.217 --> 07:33.985
Olivia,
tell your dad what's wrong.

07:33.987 --> 07:36.988
[ chuckles ]

07:36.990 --> 07:38.590
We're going to lose
the election.

07:38.592 --> 07:43.495
And I can't fix it
or make it okay.

07:43.497 --> 07:45.464
I thought I could repair
what we did,

07:45.466 --> 07:50.035
I thought we could win clean,
but...We're going to lose.

07:50.037 --> 07:53.004
I wish there was something
I could do to help.

07:53.006 --> 07:57.642
You...Don't want fitz to win.
You hate him.

07:57.644 --> 07:59.211
I do not like him.

07:59.213 --> 08:01.213
[ sighs ]
but, olivia,

08:01.215 --> 08:02.881
I do love you,

08:02.883 --> 08:06.184
And I want you to have
everything --

08:06.186 --> 08:12.190
So, when I say I wish I could
help, I do wish I could help.

08:12.192 --> 08:15.160
I wish I could help <i>you.</i>

08:21.601 --> 08:23.235
[ inhales sharply ]

08:23.237 --> 08:25.604
[ voice breaking ]
I was scared.

08:27.840 --> 08:29.674
When I saw the blood...

08:29.676 --> 08:34.079
When she stabbed you,
I was scared.

08:54.000 --> 08:56.134
Maya wants you to tie up
loose ends, huh?

08:56.136 --> 08:58.537
And I'm one of them?
Save the sentimentality.

08:58.539 --> 09:00.305
It will make it easier
on both of us.
Oh, I'm not being sentimental.

09:00.307 --> 09:02.007
Once she gets her hands
on that money,

09:02.009 --> 09:03.842
You're gonna be a loose end,
too, I promise you.

09:03.844 --> 09:07.546
You think I can just let you go?
Don't be naive.

09:07.548 --> 09:09.314
You know
our whole plan, h.

09:09.316 --> 09:11.316
You have our brokerage accounts,
routing numbers --

09:11.318 --> 09:12.784
Everything you need
to walk out of here

09:12.786 --> 09:14.553
And up the steps
to the justice department.

09:14.555 --> 09:15.654
I wouldn't do that.
I'll keep quiet.

09:15.656 --> 09:18.990
Save my life...

09:18.992 --> 09:21.660
And I'll save yours.

09:21.662 --> 09:23.228
[ elevator bell dings ]

09:25.565 --> 09:28.567
[ sighs ] we're going to
lose the election.
Maya's in the wind.

09:28.569 --> 09:30.569
What about tracking
her brokerage accounts?
All dead ends.

09:30.571 --> 09:32.737
And you never found adnan?
No luck there, either.

09:32.739 --> 09:34.806
[ sighs ]
[ moaning ]

09:38.010 --> 09:40.145
Oh, dear lord!
My eyes!

09:40.147 --> 09:41.613
[ both breathing heavily ]

09:41.615 --> 09:43.181
We thought you weren't
gonna be in till later.

09:43.183 --> 09:45.016
Yeah, well,
you thought wrong!

09:45.018 --> 09:47.352
Okay, okay.
Never mind all -- all this.

09:47.354 --> 09:50.121
What's that?
That's liv's dad's blood.

09:50.123 --> 09:52.090
He got stabbed by liv's mom
when he lured her here.

09:52.092 --> 09:54.359
Which...
Turned you two on?

09:54.361 --> 09:56.828
I--
you know what?
I don't want to know!

09:56.830 --> 09:58.763
Never mind.
Just clean up!

09:58.765 --> 10:02.233
That. [ scoffs ]
and that!

10:02.235 --> 10:04.836
[ sighs ]
[ knock on door ]

10:04.838 --> 10:07.238
What are
you doing here?

10:07.240 --> 10:10.342
That cyrus beene
let that church blow up?

10:10.344 --> 10:11.943
What are you doing here?
Because I've been watching tv,

10:11.945 --> 10:14.946
And his name doesn't seem to be
all over the news.

10:14.948 --> 10:17.616
So it's okay with you
that he was gonna let
hundreds of people die?

10:17.618 --> 10:19.250
I'm sure
he had his reasons.

10:19.252 --> 10:22.621
Homeland security's
all over it.
Homeland security?

10:22.623 --> 10:26.091
They'll bury this whole thing
under eight tons of paperwork,

10:26.093 --> 10:28.226
And voldemort gets away
scot-free again.

10:28.228 --> 10:30.261
Seems to me you did pretty well
by voldemort.

10:30.263 --> 10:31.896
Voldemort
gave you your job.

10:31.898 --> 10:36.267
The administration, b613 --
we need to get hard evidence,

10:36.269 --> 10:38.069
Build an airtight case,

10:38.071 --> 10:39.904
Make these people pay
for their crimes.

10:39.906 --> 10:44.709
You're just gonna run across
a big box of irrefutable proof?

10:44.711 --> 10:48.213
Rosen, I killed three people
right in front of you.

10:48.215 --> 10:49.280
I'm not a good guy.

10:49.282 --> 10:51.249
Deep down,
I think you are.

10:53.786 --> 10:55.320
For the first time
in my adult life,

10:55.322 --> 10:57.989
I'm no longer the property
of the United States government.

10:57.991 --> 11:00.959
Looking to enjoy collecting
his unemployment checks.

11:00.961 --> 11:02.661
So I'm gonna do
what regular guys do.

11:02.663 --> 11:04.696
I'm gonna sit down on this
couch, I'm gonna drink a beer,

11:04.698 --> 11:06.431
And I'm gonna watch the redskins
lose to the cowboys.

11:06.433 --> 11:08.366
You're welcome to join me,
rosen.

11:08.368 --> 11:10.068
Or you can go home
and stew about the fact

11:10.070 --> 11:12.037
That the bad guys
run the world.

11:12.039 --> 11:15.173
[ sighs ]

11:21.347 --> 11:24.816
I never
wanted to hurt you.

11:24.818 --> 11:26.985
Yeah, well...

11:26.987 --> 11:29.354
I've got something
for you.

11:29.356 --> 11:32.891
Only it's not actually for you.
It's for huck.

11:32.893 --> 11:35.226
What is it?
Something he wants
more than anything.

11:35.228 --> 11:38.063
Why would you give huck
something he wants?

11:38.065 --> 11:42.200
Of happiness you and your
brand-new boyfriend might have.

11:42.202 --> 11:44.803
[ clicks tongue ] what can
I say? I'm a sore loser.

11:44.805 --> 11:46.805
I'm not gonna open it.

11:46.807 --> 11:50.141
Doesn't matter, robin.
Open it. Don't open it.

11:50.143 --> 11:51.309
It'll eat away at you
either way.

11:51.311 --> 11:53.978
Just 'cause
you know it exists.

11:53.980 --> 11:55.380
See you around.

11:59.285 --> 12:01.486
[ sighs ]

12:08.060 --> 12:12.197
I'm writing the speech
you asked me to write.

12:12.199 --> 12:15.266
Uniting the party.
For sally.

12:15.268 --> 12:18.436
Do you want to read it?

12:26.245 --> 12:28.079
We can move to vermont.

12:28.081 --> 12:30.081
What?

12:30.083 --> 12:31.983
Once I lose the election.

12:31.985 --> 12:35.320
We can move to vermont.

12:35.322 --> 12:38.089
I can be the mayor,
and you --

12:38.091 --> 12:39.390
I can make jam.

12:41.260 --> 12:44.496
What about mellie?

12:44.498 --> 12:45.964
What about her?

12:45.966 --> 12:48.366
You can't just --
divorce her?

12:48.368 --> 12:52.036
Yes, I can.

12:52.038 --> 12:55.273
Liv.

12:55.275 --> 12:57.175
I am going to marry you.

12:57.177 --> 13:00.478
We are going to
have babies.

13:04.884 --> 13:06.518
Two babies, I think.

13:06.520 --> 13:10.188
[ chuckles ]

13:14.493 --> 13:15.860
Fitz --

13:15.862 --> 13:18.329
I have no allegiance
to mellie.

13:18.331 --> 13:20.198
I don't want to have
an allegiance to her.

13:20.200 --> 13:23.201
She's a vindictive, grasping,
power-hungry monster

13:23.203 --> 13:24.836
Who cares more
about the presidency

13:24.838 --> 13:26.404
Than she does about me.
That's not true.

13:26.406 --> 13:28.406
You know her.

13:28.408 --> 13:32.277
You've seen her.

13:32.279 --> 13:35.246
It's true.
The woman never loved me.

13:35.248 --> 13:38.283
She loved
what I could give her --
stop.

13:38.285 --> 13:40.418
Liv?

13:40.420 --> 13:44.255
I...

13:44.257 --> 13:47.859
Mellie asked me
not to tell you this, but I --

13:52.231 --> 13:54.065
I think...

13:54.067 --> 13:55.466
What?

13:57.336 --> 13:58.903
What?!

14:03.008 --> 14:05.410
[ sighs ]

14:07.346 --> 14:10.114
Big jerry raped her.

14:13.085 --> 14:14.219
That's a lie.

14:14.221 --> 14:17.922
She told you a lie.
Think about it.

14:17.924 --> 14:20.925
Think about who big jerry was
and how he...

14:20.927 --> 14:24.562
I believe her, fitz.

14:24.564 --> 14:26.097
I believe her.

14:26.099 --> 14:28.099
When you were running
for governor,

14:28.101 --> 14:30.101
Your father
raped mellie.

14:47.920 --> 14:49.387
[ inhales sharply ]

14:49.389 --> 14:51.456
[ sighs ]

15:01.000 --> 15:03.368
What?

15:08.140 --> 15:10.275
[ breathes shakily ]

15:10.277 --> 15:12.510
You know.

15:14.513 --> 15:16.681
I know.

15:16.683 --> 15:20.418
Olivia pope
can't do anything right.

15:23.055 --> 15:25.223
So?
[ clears throat ]

15:25.225 --> 15:27.358
Now what?

15:27.360 --> 15:30.461
[ sighs ]

15:45.544 --> 15:49.247
I took a paternity test.
That doesn't matter.

15:49.249 --> 15:53.318
Jerry is your son --
not his. Yours.
I don't care.

15:57.423 --> 16:00.325
I fought him.

16:02.194 --> 16:05.330
[ whimpers ]
I...Fought.

16:05.332 --> 16:08.099
Shh.
[ breathing shakily ]

16:21.281 --> 16:25.116
To decide who will be the next
president of the United States.

16:25.118 --> 16:26.284
The <i>times</i> is predicting
that sally langston

16:26.286 --> 16:28.453
Will be
the first female candidate

16:28.455 --> 16:30.588
To be elected
president of the United States.

16:30.590 --> 16:32.757
I'm confident because
we've seen this time and again.

16:32.759 --> 16:34.993
As undecideds finally
engage in the race,

16:34.995 --> 16:38.396
The vice president spiked
5 points yesterday!

16:38.398 --> 16:40.331
And she'll go up
even more today

16:40.333 --> 16:42.767
After the leadership test she
just passed with flying colors.

16:42.769 --> 16:44.469
And I'm afraid we're gonna
have to leave it there

16:44.471 --> 16:46.537
And hold that thought till after
this break. Stay with us.

16:51.010 --> 16:53.511
Leo:
Cyrus, cyrus, cyrus!

16:53.513 --> 16:56.180
When is the last time
the polls were wrong?

16:56.182 --> 16:57.648
Dewey v. Truman?

16:57.650 --> 16:59.650
If you're gonna send your little
redheaded minion out there

16:59.652 --> 17:01.486
Under the hot lights,
at least give her some ammo

17:01.488 --> 17:04.555
That's not from
before the korean war.

17:08.460 --> 17:11.462
I'm sorry.
Don't be.

17:11.464 --> 17:15.133
You said you'd end up here,
and you were right.

17:15.135 --> 17:18.536
So I say,
to the victor go the spoils.

17:21.640 --> 17:24.509
Hmm.
[ sniffs ]

17:24.511 --> 17:27.378
[ glasses clink ]

17:27.380 --> 17:30.381
Any words of advice?

17:30.383 --> 17:33.217
Nope.
[ sniffs ]

17:33.219 --> 17:37.055
Well, maybe.

17:37.057 --> 17:41.359
Try and protect your soul,
if you still have one.

17:41.361 --> 17:46.064
It's futile,
but...You should still try.

17:46.066 --> 17:49.534
Soul. Got it.

17:49.536 --> 17:51.769
You single, leo?

17:51.771 --> 17:55.139
Divorced.
Good.

17:55.141 --> 17:58.676
Best if you don't have a family
in this job.

18:01.513 --> 18:03.815
[ crickets chirping ]
what is this?

18:03.817 --> 18:05.650
Why are we here?

18:09.321 --> 18:13.091
Huck. If I know something
important, you should, too.

18:13.093 --> 18:15.426
The mom is kimberly.

18:15.428 --> 18:19.430
Ohh, I don't want to watch
a new family.

18:19.432 --> 18:21.566
The mom is kimberly.

18:21.568 --> 18:24.435
Went back to school a few years
ago. Now she's a lawyer.

18:24.437 --> 18:25.770
She owns
the house outright.

18:25.772 --> 18:27.605
Got a special v.A. Loan
to pay for it.

18:27.607 --> 18:29.540
The boy is...
Javi.

18:29.542 --> 18:32.844
He's 12.
And he likes to skateboard.

18:32.846 --> 18:34.512
And -- and he's really good
at "world of warcraft."

18:34.514 --> 18:38.116
He's -- he's an honor student.
What is wrong with you?!

18:38.118 --> 18:41.185
Huck --
what is wrong with you?!

18:41.187 --> 18:42.753
Why would you bring me here
and show me...

18:42.755 --> 18:45.123
What is wrong with you?!

18:45.125 --> 18:47.191
I wanted you to know --

18:47.193 --> 18:51.362
I love you, huck,
and I wanted you to know.

18:51.364 --> 18:54.732
Okay --
don't you ever speak
another word to me again.

18:58.170 --> 18:59.704
[ breathes heavily ]

19:02.207 --> 19:04.208
Where are you?
When are you getting here?

19:04.210 --> 19:06.878
Olivia: I'm not.
I'm not going to come.

19:06.880 --> 19:08.546
Liv --
my mother blew up the church

19:08.548 --> 19:10.548
That's costing you
your presidency.

19:10.550 --> 19:12.416
I shouldn't be there.

19:12.418 --> 19:15.286
How's your father?
Drugged.

19:15.288 --> 19:17.488
I think
he was in pain earlier.

19:17.490 --> 19:19.390
I wish I could be there
with you.

19:19.392 --> 19:20.658
No, you don't.

19:20.660 --> 19:22.527
No place in the world
I'd rather be.

19:24.696 --> 19:27.765
This is the last big speech
I'll ever give.

19:27.767 --> 19:30.434
You'll do great.

19:30.436 --> 19:32.236
You think?

19:32.238 --> 19:34.372
[ chuckles ]

19:34.374 --> 19:36.541
Remember to breathe,
make eye contact,

19:36.543 --> 19:38.242
Acknowledge mellie
and your kids.

19:38.244 --> 19:41.245
Be warm, be honest.

19:41.247 --> 19:43.247
You don't need me
to tell you any of this.

19:43.249 --> 19:45.550
You're the best politician
in the game.

19:48.854 --> 19:51.455
Liv --
it's okay.

19:53.425 --> 19:56.761
Vermont's not happening.
I understand.

19:56.763 --> 19:59.530
You can't
leave her now.

20:02.868 --> 20:04.602
Not yet.

20:07.472 --> 20:08.940
I wouldn't want you

20:08.942 --> 20:13.511
If, knowing what you know,
you left her now.

20:16.782 --> 20:18.382
I love you.

20:20.285 --> 20:21.819
I love you, too.

20:25.490 --> 20:29.827
Just stay here on the phone
with me a minute.

20:29.829 --> 20:32.263
Okay.

20:54.653 --> 20:58.656
[ voice breaking ]
I'm going to hang up now.

20:58.658 --> 21:01.592
[ beep ]

21:06.832 --> 21:09.667
[ monitor beeping ]

21:09.669 --> 21:11.836
Was that your boyfriend?

21:11.838 --> 21:13.537
I'm calling security.

21:13.539 --> 21:15.006
Livvie, you probably
won't understand

21:15.008 --> 21:16.841
Until you have
kids of your own,

21:16.843 --> 21:19.377
But...
I did this for you.

21:19.379 --> 21:22.446
Woman: And it's those hopes,
those dreams...

21:22.448 --> 21:28.586
...Here in the United States
of america...
...I was about to throw up.

21:28.588 --> 21:30.021
You get used to it.
...Thanks to a leader

21:30.023 --> 21:33.524
That leader is here tonight.
I'm sorry you're going to lose.

21:33.526 --> 21:34.992
Jerry!
And I am so honored
to be introducing him.

21:34.994 --> 21:37.828
[ chuckling ] really?
This from a reston supporter?

21:37.830 --> 21:39.997
Woman: Now please give
a warm springfield welcome

21:39.999 --> 21:42.500
To the president
of the United States of america,

21:42.502 --> 21:45.002
Fitzgerald grant iii!

21:45.004 --> 21:46.671
[ cheers and applause ]

21:46.673 --> 21:51.509
Maya: That man hurts you.
He uses you.

21:51.511 --> 21:54.412
And he will throw you away
when he's done with you.

21:54.414 --> 21:57.381
I just wanted to give you
the chance to be free,

21:57.383 --> 21:59.417
To be happy.

21:59.419 --> 22:01.052
Fitz: We all know we're on
the cusp of another election.

22:01.054 --> 22:03.587
And it's an important one.

22:03.589 --> 22:05.890
And I hope you all vote --
ideally for me.

22:05.892 --> 22:07.925
[ laughter ]
olivia: Was any of it real?

22:07.927 --> 22:09.760
You and dad?
You and me?

22:09.762 --> 22:11.862
The first 12 years of my life?
Was any of that real?

22:11.864 --> 22:14.865
I am proud of the work
we have achieved...
I didn't kill him.

22:14.867 --> 22:16.567
...But I am humbled
by the tasks still ahead...

22:16.569 --> 22:18.569
And we both know
I could have.

22:18.571 --> 22:22.707
[ sneezes ]
...First and foremost of which
is finding and punishing

22:22.709 --> 22:26.410
And who's gonna stop me,
sweetie?
...On our own soil
yesterday afternoon.

22:26.412 --> 22:27.511
You?

22:27.513 --> 22:28.579
[ crowd chanting "grant" ]

22:28.581 --> 22:31.982
[ cheers and applause ]

22:31.984 --> 22:33.984
Fitz!

22:33.986 --> 22:36.387
Are you gonna stop me?

22:36.988 --> 22:38.689
Fitz?!

22:38.691 --> 22:42.026
[ chanting continues ]

22:44.029 --> 22:45.463
Fitz:
And we will find them!

22:45.465 --> 22:48.099
Fitz!

22:48.101 --> 22:51.068
[ all gasp ]

22:54.841 --> 22:59.810
<i>Where jerry grant, the</i>
<i>president's 15-year-old son,</i>

22:59.812 --> 23:02.146
<i>Collapsed onstage</i>
<i>during a campaign rally.</i>

23:02.148 --> 23:03.814
Campbell: <i>The president's son</i>
<i>was immediately rushed</i>

23:03.816 --> 23:07.518
<i>Where he suffered a seizure</i>
<i>shortly after his arrival.</i>

23:07.520 --> 23:11.956
<i>We are still waiting</i>
<i>for a statement</i>

23:11.958 --> 23:13.824
<i>From the white house</i>
<i>as to his condition.</i>

23:13.826 --> 23:17.128
Despite the exhaustive efforts
of a world-class medical team,

23:17.130 --> 23:19.663
Fitzgerald thomas grant iv

23:19.665 --> 23:24.802
Passed away at 8:46 p.M.
From bacterial meningitis.

23:24.804 --> 23:27.004
He was surrounded
by president grant,

23:27.006 --> 23:30.007
The first lady,
his sister, karen...

23:32.477 --> 23:35.179
We're going to win
the election now.

23:37.716 --> 23:39.750
They lost their child.

23:39.752 --> 23:42.186
America will rally
behind them.

23:42.188 --> 23:45.589
We're going to win. I hadn't
really thought about it.

23:45.591 --> 23:47.958
I did.

23:47.960 --> 23:50.494
A child is dead,

23:50.496 --> 23:54.832
And that's the first thing
that popped into my head.

23:54.834 --> 23:58.436
I was going to let that church
blow up with everyone in it.

24:06.912 --> 24:09.747
How did we get
like this?

24:09.749 --> 24:13.217
When did
we stop being people?

24:13.219 --> 24:17.021
Were we ever people?

24:17.023 --> 24:20.057
Or did serving at the pleasure
of the president

24:20.059 --> 24:22.593
Just help us to shed
our pesky skins

24:22.595 --> 24:26.664
And unmask us
as the monsters we really are?

24:33.205 --> 24:35.639
[ sniffles ]

24:43.548 --> 24:46.750
Did you see his face?

24:46.752 --> 24:49.820
When he was carrying
his son?

24:52.591 --> 24:55.726
Did you see it?

24:55.728 --> 24:57.795
Yeah.

25:01.600 --> 25:05.135
I saw it.

25:07.706 --> 25:09.874
Mr. President.

25:09.876 --> 25:12.676
I have some information
regarding jerry.

25:12.678 --> 25:15.112
The autopsy revealed
an infection from meningitis b.

25:15.114 --> 25:18.549
In this case, the cdc
traced it to a sub-strain

25:18.551 --> 25:20.818
Which is kept under lock and key
in fort detrick.

25:20.820 --> 25:24.755
Apparently a vial of it
went missing this week.

25:26.858 --> 25:29.260
My son was murdered?

25:35.835 --> 25:39.203
You're not listening to me.
You're not listening to <i>me.</i>

25:39.205 --> 25:40.738
Let him through.

25:47.579 --> 25:49.914
You should be in bed.

25:49.916 --> 25:51.849
So should you.

25:56.688 --> 26:00.090
They sedated her.
My daughter, too.

26:00.092 --> 26:02.259
They wanted to sedate me,
but...

26:02.261 --> 26:05.629
[ sighs ]
...I don't see that happening.

26:05.631 --> 26:07.097
Especially not now.

26:07.099 --> 26:10.000
Mr. President --
it was maya pope.

26:12.771 --> 26:15.639
They've connected her
to a bacterial strain

26:15.641 --> 26:17.808
That was stolen
from fort detrick yesterday.

26:17.810 --> 26:20.744
She missed me
at the church...

26:20.746 --> 26:23.581
So she went after jerry.

26:24.950 --> 26:27.952
She killed my son.

26:27.954 --> 26:30.955
And now I'm going to
kill her.

26:30.957 --> 26:33.123
You can't do it yourself.

26:33.125 --> 26:36.694
Not you or homeland security
or the fbi.

26:36.696 --> 26:39.363
Official channels
means official remedies,

26:39.365 --> 26:41.865
None of which will give you
what you want.
Which is?

26:41.867 --> 26:43.734
You're not looking for justice,
mr. President.

26:43.736 --> 26:45.936
You're looking for a head
served on a platter.

26:45.938 --> 26:48.706
Are you saying
you can get that for me?

26:48.708 --> 26:49.840
I may not be your friend,
mr. President,

26:49.842 --> 26:52.943
I know what I would do
if someone hurt my child.

26:52.945 --> 26:55.179
Yes,
I will get that for you.

26:56.781 --> 26:58.849
Do it.
Olivia: Dad?

27:04.289 --> 27:07.291
What's going on?

27:07.293 --> 27:10.828
[ gasping ]
you're not your mother.
It's not your fault.

27:10.830 --> 27:12.196
It's not your fault.
I know better than anyone

27:12.198 --> 27:15.699
I need to go check on my family.
I don't hold it against you.

27:15.701 --> 27:17.101
I don't blame you.
I need to go check on my family.

27:17.103 --> 27:20.671
You're not responsible for this.
You're not your mother.

27:20.673 --> 27:23.841
It's not your fault. Your fault.
I need to go check on my family.

27:23.843 --> 27:26.844
[ crying ]

27:31.983 --> 27:34.118
Early exit polls are
just starting to come in.

27:34.120 --> 27:38.322
There seems to be a swell
of support for president grant.

27:38.324 --> 27:40.290
Sir, you should lie down.
Get some rest.

27:40.292 --> 27:41.892
You're gonna win
this election.

27:41.894 --> 27:44.228
And when you do,
it's gonna be a madhouse.

27:44.230 --> 27:47.231
As someone
who just lost his husband...

27:47.233 --> 27:49.733
It'll hit you
when you least expect it.

27:49.735 --> 27:51.201
I know you want to keep moving,
keep your mind off --

27:51.203 --> 27:54.972
I lost a child.

28:09.054 --> 28:10.888
Hey.

28:12.857 --> 28:16.694
What did we say?

28:16.696 --> 28:19.863
No more drinking.

28:19.865 --> 28:21.832
I wasn't there for him.

28:21.834 --> 28:24.168
I kept my distance
from him.

28:24.170 --> 28:29.907
Because I was terrified
of what he might...Be.

28:32.177 --> 28:36.213
It turns out...
He was yours.

28:36.215 --> 28:40.217
The whole time.

28:40.219 --> 28:42.953
But he was always mine.

28:42.955 --> 28:44.955
Or he should have been.

28:44.957 --> 28:49.193
But I was afraid,
and now he's gone.

28:56.134 --> 28:59.803
[ gasps ]
I wanted to knock so bad,
but I didn't.

28:59.805 --> 29:00.838
I couldn't.

29:00.840 --> 29:02.206
Huck.

29:04.342 --> 29:06.243
Quinn found my family.

29:08.246 --> 29:12.316
I think they look well.
They look good.

29:12.318 --> 29:15.419
Huck, you should
try to talk to them.

29:15.421 --> 29:19.256
No. No. It's a bad idea.
I'm not going to.

29:19.258 --> 29:24.294
Talk to them. No.
They love you.

29:24.296 --> 29:30.901
Maybe that's good.
It's good to be dead.

29:30.903 --> 29:33.871
It's good for me
to be dead.

29:33.873 --> 29:36.340
I have a good life now.

29:36.342 --> 29:38.308
And my family
has a good life now.

29:38.310 --> 29:39.977
No one is lying to them.

29:39.979 --> 29:42.279
No one is torturing people
all day

29:42.281 --> 29:45.249
And then coming home
and pretending to be normal.

29:45.251 --> 29:47.951
No one is hunting them,
trying to get at me.

29:47.953 --> 29:49.419
No one is
trying to kill them.

29:49.421 --> 29:52.256
They are safe.
It's better for them.

29:52.258 --> 29:58.128
Starting over, starting fresh,
it's better for me.

29:58.130 --> 30:02.800
I get to be...
Someone else...

30:02.802 --> 30:04.268
Someone new.

30:04.270 --> 30:08.138
Oh.

30:08.140 --> 30:11.875
Me leaving them behind?

30:11.877 --> 30:16.246
That was the best thing
that's ever happened to them.

30:24.088 --> 30:27.324
[ crying ]
they look good.

30:31.262 --> 30:34.231
I'm fine.
I checked myself out.

30:34.233 --> 30:37.234
Against the doctor's orders.
I would have driven you home.

30:37.236 --> 30:40.404
You would have made me stay.
I have a job to do.

30:40.406 --> 30:43.307
Do you have any leads
on mom?

30:43.309 --> 30:46.343
I'm not discussing that
with you.

30:46.345 --> 30:47.477
I want you
to stay clean on this.

30:47.479 --> 30:49.513
I do not
want you involved.

30:49.515 --> 30:52.416
Okay.

30:55.220 --> 30:56.620
Olivia?

30:59.257 --> 31:01.925
That plane
you got for me,

31:01.927 --> 31:06.897
The plane
and the new life --

31:06.899 --> 31:09.266
Does that offer
still stand?

31:09.268 --> 31:11.501
[ sighs ]

31:11.503 --> 31:13.637
Abby: No!

31:13.639 --> 31:16.173
I don't accept this.
You don't quit.

31:16.175 --> 31:18.108
Olivia pope
doesn't quit.

31:18.110 --> 31:20.210
I'm done.
I can't do this anymore.

31:20.212 --> 31:22.880
You have to at least wait
for harrison to get back or...

31:22.882 --> 31:24.047
Say something!

31:24.049 --> 31:25.315
When are you going?

31:25.317 --> 31:29.286
Now. Today.
Abby, this is for the best.

31:29.288 --> 31:31.588
Over a cliff, liv!
Over a cliff!

31:31.590 --> 31:33.290
We went over a cliff
for you,

31:33.292 --> 31:35.125
And you just --
you walk out on us?!

31:35.127 --> 31:38.428
You'll be taken care of
financially, anything you need.

31:38.430 --> 31:40.230
By who? By who?!

31:40.232 --> 31:42.432
My father has said
he will take care of everything.

31:42.434 --> 31:44.268
We haven't found
your mother yet.

31:44.270 --> 31:45.936
My father is on it.
He'll find her.

31:45.938 --> 31:47.204
Your father
is a monster.

31:47.206 --> 31:50.340
He's a murderer and a liar
and a criminal.

31:50.342 --> 31:53.076
You hate him, and now you're
trusting him with your life?

31:53.078 --> 31:54.177
He's my father.

31:54.179 --> 31:56.513
[ keys jingle ]
take these.

31:56.515 --> 31:58.415
Everything else you need
is in the safe.

32:01.052 --> 32:03.053
Just go.

32:03.055 --> 32:04.354
Run to daddy.

32:09.560 --> 32:10.961
[ sighs ]

32:22.106 --> 32:25.342
[ alarm chirps ]

32:29.647 --> 32:31.348
Just the man
I was looking for.

32:34.118 --> 32:36.353
Tell me everything you know
about maya and adnan salif.

32:36.355 --> 32:38.355
I can't do that.
Because of your allegiance
to ms. Salif.

32:38.357 --> 32:39.523
Because
you don't trust me.

32:39.525 --> 32:41.058
Because you don't
yet understand

32:41.060 --> 32:43.293
That you are in
way over your head.

32:47.966 --> 32:49.633
Adnan's dead?

32:49.635 --> 32:51.635
Maya got to her the
same way that she got
to the president's son.

32:51.637 --> 32:53.337
That is who you
are dealing with.

32:53.339 --> 32:55.305
That is why you are in
over your head.

32:55.307 --> 33:00.310
Let me help you because
now we both want the same thing.

33:06.351 --> 33:10.020
I know where maya's planning
on collecting her cash.

33:10.022 --> 33:13.023
You quit o.P.A.?

33:16.661 --> 33:18.328
You're leaving?

33:18.330 --> 33:20.630
Abby called you?

33:20.632 --> 33:22.165
Huck called me.

33:22.167 --> 33:24.501
Huck, of all people,
should understand.

33:24.503 --> 33:25.502
[ tape rips ]

33:25.504 --> 33:28.038
Understand what?
Forget it.

33:28.040 --> 33:29.606
No, understand what?
It's me.

33:29.608 --> 33:32.743
Everything
that's happened.

33:32.745 --> 33:35.112
None of it would be happening
if it weren't for me.

33:35.114 --> 33:37.414
It's my mother, my father,
the man I love,

33:37.416 --> 33:41.118
An innocent boy dying,
churches blowing up,

33:41.120 --> 33:42.319
You being thrown
in the hole.

33:42.321 --> 33:44.354
The only common denominator
is me.

33:44.356 --> 33:46.690
I'm at the center.
I'm the eye of the storm.

33:46.692 --> 33:49.226
So you're the devil.
Is that it?

33:49.228 --> 33:50.327
And this is
your pity party?

33:50.329 --> 33:54.331
You should go.

33:54.333 --> 33:56.199
You're not leaving.

34:00.104 --> 34:01.805
This is
not a pity party.

34:01.807 --> 34:05.642
This is me doing
what I do best.

34:05.644 --> 34:08.178
I'm handling this.
I'm fixing this.

34:08.180 --> 34:10.380
I have been over
every option.

34:10.382 --> 34:12.249
I have looked at it
from every angle,

34:12.251 --> 34:14.251
And I have hoped and prayed
that I was wrong.

34:14.253 --> 34:16.086
I have tried to pretend
that I didn't know

34:16.088 --> 34:20.223
So now it's time for me
to stand in my truth.

34:20.225 --> 34:21.725
It's me.

34:21.727 --> 34:24.561
I'm the thing
that needs to be fixed,

34:24.563 --> 34:26.229
I'm the thing that needs to
be handled.

34:26.231 --> 34:28.098
I'm the scandal.

34:28.100 --> 34:29.733
And the best way to deal
with a scandal

34:29.735 --> 34:32.836
Is to shut it down.

34:32.838 --> 34:36.339
Take me with you.

34:36.341 --> 34:40.210
[ sighs ]

34:40.212 --> 34:42.245
Jake...

34:42.247 --> 34:45.115
Take me with you.

34:45.117 --> 34:47.651
Run away with me.
Save me.

34:49.787 --> 34:54.758
I am in love
with someone else.

34:54.760 --> 34:57.227
You're leaving
everything else behind.

34:57.229 --> 34:59.262
Leave that behind,
too.

34:59.264 --> 35:01.098
Don't go alone.
You don't have to be alone.

35:03.835 --> 35:07.471
You want to stand in the sun
with me.

35:07.473 --> 35:10.574
I want us to stand
in the sun together.

